“All Will Be Revealed…”</h3><!--EZCODE HTML END--><br>
A couple of weeks before the Cairpre incident, Ienoldar had asked me if I thought of breaking away and maybe starting our own guild. I had told him that I had put so much into this guild that it felt like mine and I wanted to see if we could make it work.  But the idea had already occurred to me and would bounce around in my brain for some time.  After, Cairpre was ousted, Ienoldar left a post on our website.  <br>
<br>
“The time has come when I have to make a stand.   For the past months I've been thinking about staying or leaving the Stormcallers. And as of today I have made my decision to take the final step out of the guild. Don't misunderstand me, I love you guys with all of my heart and I really enjoyed being out in the field with you.  But the guild is too unorganized for my taste   There is no planning what so ever from the leader before the raids.  Most of the times we don't even have a leader at the raids.   I really like you as a person Xellosx but you must admit that you failed as our leader.   I want to through a BIG thank you to all of you Especially Kamdar who have been putting in tons of hours on the web design to keep the guild together.  Best of luck to all of you in the future.  The Stormcaller has left the building.”<br>
<br>
Cairpre , who was still keeping an eye on our board , then chimed in with “Xell this will prolly make you NEVER wanna let me back in the guild but as Ienoldar has stated  you have failed as a leader to us, you hardly ever show up at the raids, your never on, and well your mean.....Xell if I were you I would hand over my position as guild leader to someone more capable of doing the job.”<br>
<br>
Xell’s responded as eloquently as ever,” You are dumb....I haven’t failed anything... let the people who doubt go.. and Cairpre you will never ever be a leader or an officer to any guild... they would kick you out faster then I did... I'm right here.. what now huh?”<br>
<br>
I was a little shocked by Ienoldar’s sudden departure, though it was not totally unexpected.  I had hoped that when or if it came time to leave, that several of us would plan ahead and do it at once.  Now one of the Officers had already left.  Also, Ien had been my first recruit and I was saddened to see him leave.<br>
<br>
While all this was going on, Officer Arrwen had been quietly beefing up our ranks with some of her good friends.  She invited Arathain, Cobo, Niarki, and her brother Wamphyre into the guild.  Little did I know that every one of these new members would play an important part in our future. However, at present, they were all a little too new to be considered for our now vacant officer position.  <br>
<br>
And so, at my request, Wiggam Wauggam stood before Xellosx and several of the other officers of the Stormcallers.  Including myself, Erdrix and Eilonen were there.<br>
<br>
The discussion turned into more of an interview of Xellosx, as Wiggam wondered if he really wanted to be an officer, serving under him.  “What are your plans and goals for our guild?” Wiggam asked. <br>
<br>
Xellosx responded with, “My plans will all be revealed within due time”<br>
<br>
“Sounds like you are being evasive.  Why so dark and mysterious?”<br>
<br>
“Yes, I am dark, but it is really none of your concern.”<br>
<br>
The conversation went on like that for some time.  Wiggam was putting Xell through his paces!  At one point he even called him a little twisted.  Erdrix leaned over and whispered in Xell’s ear, “Wigs acting like a dick to you, yes..but his intentions are valorous... and you know it.”   <br>
<br>
Xellosx was obviously becoming annoyed.  After the meeting he had a discussion with me. <br>
<br>
“Kam, I am not too pleased”<br>
<br>
“Because Wig has concerns and questions?” I asked.<br>
<br>
“Oh its so much more then that Kam.... I don't appreciate people trying to rival me  ...I don’t appreciate being threatened.. and I sure as hell don’t like attitude directed at me.  Even Eilonen just commented on Wiggam, and Erdrix wasn’t too happy either.”<br>
<br>
I must have missed something…”What threats?  He was asking about goals and intentions of the guild, was he not?  Isn't it wise to know what one stands for?”<br>
<br>
Xellosx responded, “Kam, it almost seems like you don’t believe me.  Do you have any resentment towards me Kam? Honestly?”<br>
<br>
I ignored the resentment question and countered with “Do you like blind followers...or people that have opinions, and mutual respect?”<br>
<br>
“We have no blind followers in our guild.” He said flatly.<br>
<br>
“Truthfully I have been worried about the future of the guild.  Sometimes I have felt like the only one working at it.” I said.<br>
<br>
Now it was Xell’s turn to ignore my statement, “Come on Kam you are older then I am, surely you could tell what he was trying to do...”<br>
<br>
I played dumb, ‘I am sorry, maybe its the beers, but no, what was he trying to do?”<br>
<br>
“In my opinion, and that of Eilonen and Erd, he was trying to one up me every step of the way.” Since Eilonen and Erd were no longer in the room, Xell had no problem speaking for them.  <br>
<br>
“All I know is that he took his time deciding whether to join this guild...I think it was an important decision for him.  If we cannot talk frankly, then we cannot talk at all.”<br>
<br>
Xellosx countered, “Frank is one thing, being a dick is another.”<br>
<br>
“I do not think he was being a dick, from what I saw all his questions were valid.”<br>
<br>
“Yes they all were.. but Kam thats not even what I am talking about man, it was the attitude, the feeling you get... he had to use all these bigass words and try and one up me, twist my words around.  He'll never match me!”<br>
<br>
“I also feel you were being a little cryptic....’All will be revealed...’  Huh?”<br>
<br>
“Dude he was being the same way I wonder how you could only notice me when everyone else seemed to have noticed him.  The nerve to call me dark and twisted... even if I am dark and twisted .. sheesh”<br>
<br>
“You did kind of admit it, as I remember!”<br>
<br>
“Of course I did.. I'm not going to lie... but wtf.,.,.”<br>
<br>
I was starting to get tired of this conversation and thought I would try to wrap things up. “So, do I assume you would not want Wig as an officer?”<br>
<br>
Xell surprised me with “No, as an officer he would be great... as a friend of mine... Hah!  I don’t think so!”<br>
<br>
“That’s what makes guilds interesting.” I said.<br>
<br>
Xell agreed, “Yep... I have a feeling ES is going to get ALOT more interesting soon.”<br>
<br>
I did not say anything, but I couldn’t help but think that he was right.  And although Wiggam turned down the offer of promotion, things were indeed going to get real interesting.<br>
<br>
Xellosx then headed back to the message board…” Some of you seem to think I enjoy arguing, however you couldn’t be more wrong. I work hard in whatever time I have on ES, I want to make a great guild here.  I don’t especially like removing anyone, or seeing people leave. I already know for a fact the opinions of some of you..(even my officers) and that’s fine. But the doubting and testing me has to go.  I also find it annoying to be undermined, and being told what to do and how to do it. We are all on the same team here, under the same flag.  We're supposed to be tight like a family, but I can see that we have a ways to go before that happens.”<br>
<br>
A couple of days later Ienoldar apologized for leaving the Stormcallers and told Xellosx, “I realize how much the Stormcallers really meant to me  And Xellosx you actually showed me that you are willing to fight for this guild to be number one.  Needless to say I regret that I quit the guild.   So Xellosx, if you ever can forgive me and need someone to stand up and fight.  I'm here and I'm willing to make our dreams come true.”<br>
<br>
Xellosx welcomed Ien back with open arms and went back to his hard work of running the guild.  Essentually that meant inviting former members of Valor of Virtopia into the Eternal Stormcallers.  Varden and Ashamen were instantly named Co-Leaders.  Charleena was made an Officer.  <br>
<br>
All of them had the last name Darketernal.<br>
<br>
I guess Xellosx’s ultimate plans for the guild were finally being revealed.   The Darketernals were running the show, and they were all strangers to us.<br>
