“Welcome. If you've come this far, you probably know why you're here.”<br>
<br>
Those were my first words in the secret chamber that we had come together in (actually a hastily created message board).  I had dubbed it “The Eye of the Storm” and we referred to ourselves as The Secret Society of Stormcallers.  We were essentially, a guild within a guild.<br>
<br>
Officers Arrwen, Ienoldar and Eilonen  (as his alternate Tomani) were there. <br>
<br>
Arrwen had recruited Arathain, Cobo, Niarki, Wamphyre and a few others that had not yet joined any guild, Tanluin, Chonn and Herbdiva.  Ienoldar, had brought in his wife Angeleena as well as Bygdogg and Genene. And of course, Burak and Wiggam were there.<br>
<br>
It was fairly late in the evening, and by the time I would stop talking it would be after midnight.   But when I had started to speak, it was still July 4th.  The date did not escape me.<br>
<br>
I cleared my throat and went on. “We have come here to discuss our future with The Eternal Stormcallers and what our options might be.  As you know, I have not been very pleased with our leader Xellosx, and find it harder and harder to serve under him. I have been troubled by what I consider his lack of any of the really good qualities a leader should have.  I do not like the way he addresses his fellow guild mates on the message board. It is often in a condescending and not very respectful tone. <br>
<br>
“He seldom follows through on his plans. He has only shown up for one guild event. And he never informs the officers what his ultimate plans for the guild are.  Although several times he has referred to some master plan and all will be revealed in time. As far as I can see his only plan is to keep adding more leaders to the top of the members list with the last name of Darketernal.  I then told them of the recent letter I had received from Varden.  The one explaining the whole Darketernal sponsored guild thing. <br>
<br>
“Ok,” I went on, “Besides the fact that none of us knew this about the Darketernals going in, it is still rather insulting to see name after name added to the leaders without us knowing a thing about these guys. Varden appears to have a cool head and a much better disposition than Xellosx, and so far I have not had any problems with him. Except of course the continued secrecy of whatever it is that they think they are planning.  There is more I could complain about at this first meeting, but I think you all know what I am talking about.  So what do we do? <br>
<br>
