<br>
Arrwen said, “Wiggam, I understand how you feel and I think that is very noble of you to be up front and honest with ES. I on the other hand want to make sure all of my ducks are in a row before I approach ES with the fact that I am leaving. You are right I can easily ignore Xell. When I joined the guild we were all younguns and I felt close to many guild mates. I even liked Xell.  But I also didn’t know I was joining a family of Darketernal's. Now there is a level 6 leader Darketernal, new to the guild. I never agreed to any of these new leaders nor have I ever gotten the chance to get and know them because they all sort of pop up out of nowhere. One day they aren't a member of the guild, the next they are a leader.  The leader is someone that I think should be agreed upon. They hold the ultimate power of the guild. That's why I think I would be happy with this new guld using the leader only for management purposes (at least in the beginning) and having the guild utilize its officers. Let the officers plan raids, social events, invite members etc. The leader can take care of anyone who would abuse such powers.  Although with us all starting out small and familiar I dont believe anyone would abuse such powers.”<br>
<br>
