<br>
Then Ienoldar let us know his thoughts. “I think you all know how I felt before, when I quit The Stormcallers.  I have for a very long time been unhappy with the way the guild is working. It is very unorganized, and yes lately Xellosx have been more interested in getting his so called family members in the guild than doing something for the members.  I have discussed this issue with Kamdar before and I was even back then ready to start a new guild.  The one and only reason why I came back to ES again was you guys, I always enjoyed having such good friends out in the field.  As far as leader I agree that Wiggam is a very good choice, and he have proven this more than once.  Of course Kamdar is a very good choice as well.  The two are just full of energy and ideas and that’s what we really need.  But I think we should take this slow.  Before we start the guild we should set the rules together and make sure that everybody agrees to the decisions.  The name though...Stormcallers Elite sounds really good, so does Eye Of The Storm.&quot;<br>
<br>
Cobo then expressed concerns that maybe Burak’s idea of pointing the Stormcaller’s website to our possible new site was maybe not such a noble endeavor.  He thought it would be mean and would not support it.<br>
<br>
Arrwen agreed with him, “We don’t want to appear to any that may not know of our feelings that we are A-holes. We are just several disillusioned members that have a good amount of energy to change our feelings from disillusioned to focused. And that focus is a guild that we can be proud of. Where there are no oddities or secrets. Of course &quot;all will be revealed&quot; later!” she joked.<br>
<br>
Burak was humbled, “You are right. It was mean spirited of me to suggest it in the first place. BUT, the look on his face would have been priceless.”<br>
<br>
I too felt a little humbled. I loved Burak’s idea when I first heard it, but now realized that Cobo and Arrwen had an excellent point.<br>
<br>
Chonn, who I learned was father to Cobo, Arathain and Niarki had been taking it all in.  Now he spoke up, “I am not a member of any guild, but have three children in the Stormcallers so I was considering joining them. If my children go - and they seem to be interested, I would support your efforts. I do not know how much help I can add to your guild. My time is truly not my own. But I enjoy the game, love to explore and map, and for as much as I can be on-line, I will give 100% to the group. <br>
<br>
“In the matter of breaking away from the old group and starting a new one: I suggest that you avoid poking your finger in the other guy's eye. It's a temptation, and people are annoyed, but don't start the new with animosity towards the old. It flavors everything you do. Don't mimic their name - do something different to reflect your needs. Fellowship has been mentioned: Consider “Fellowship of the Light” “Legion of Force” or “Band of Buds.”  But don't begin the new with malice toward the old.”<br>
<br>
I think it was then that I realized how wise this barbarian was.  And also how wise, noble and thoughtful all of these other folks were too.  I was honored to be in such good company.<br>
<br>
Others then offered their support and also their own suggestions as to what we should be called.  For it appeared that we were going to move forward with this endeavor. <br>
 <br>
It wasn’t a bad start at all.<br>
